					<p class="description">
						<p class="description">
I am an interdisciplinary scientist with expertise in biology, neuroscience, and data science. I received my Ph.D. in Biology from the Institute for Neurobiology, Freie Universität Berlin (2022), and my M.Sc. in Biology from Zhejiang University, China.
</p>

<p class="description">
Throughout my academic career, I have investigated biological questions using both honeybee and human model systems. My research spans developmental biology, epidemiology, molecular pathology, natural products, animal behaviour, and human neuroscience, with particular interests in spatial memory and social cognition. Working across diverse biological systems has enabled me to approach complex scientific questions from multiple perspectives by integrating experimental, computational, and interdisciplinary approaches.
</p>

<p class="description">
My research lies at the interface of life sciences, neuroscience, data science, and artificial intelligence. I am particularly interested in integrating experimental and computational approaches to understand biological mechanisms and translate scientific discoveries into practical applications in healthcare, digital health, and health innovation. I am equally fascinated by both fundamental and applied research, believing that advances in basic science provide the foundation for meaningful innovation and real-world impact.
</p>

<p class="description">
Beyond biomedical research, I am also interested in applying data science to broader societal challenges, including healthcare systems, social welfare, public policy, and evidence-based decision-making. Integrating biological knowledge, computational methods, and real-world data can help generate innovative solutions that improve both human health and society.
</p>

<p class="description">
Outside academia, I enjoy nature-inspired crafts and creative projects. This website features my work in research, data science, and additionally, handmade crafts.
</p>	
<p class="description">
Language: 
Chinese (Native), English (Proficient), Norwegian (Proficient), German (Working limited), Hokkien/Taiwanese (Native), Cantonese (Working limited)

</p>		
</p>

